key_points: Brian Laundrie remains missing following the issuance of an arrest warrant related to Gabby Petito's death.
Search in Florida's Carlton Reserve for Laundrie continues for the sixth day, focused on the area he told his parents he was visiting.
Laundrie is indicted for unauthorized use of a Capital One debit card and pin between Aug. 30 and Sep. 1, with intent to defraud.
Commander Joseph Fussell, leading the search, states that the warrant doesn't change their strategy in finding Laundrie.
Gabby Petito's funeral is scheduled for Sunday at Moloney's Holbrook Funeral Home, open to the public and media.
Petito was reported missing on Sept. 11; her body was later found in Grand Teton National Park, her death ruled a homicide.
City of Moab, UT, investigates the police handling of a domestic incident between Petito and Laundrie on Aug. 12.
Witness Nina Celie Angelo reports an explosive argument between Petito and Laundrie at a Wyoming restaurant on Aug. 27.
Divers join the search for Laundrie in Florida, focusing on bodies of water in Carlton Reserve, though no findings reported yet.
Moab Police release a witness statement describing a domestic dispute between Petito and Laundrie in August.
spokespersons: Commander Joseph Fussell (Leading the search in Florida)
Chief Bret Edge (Moab City Police Chief)
